<p><b>What is jazz guitar comping?</b> Comping on guitar is short for "accompanying". This could refer to playing chords behind a vocalist or saxophonist, or even accompanying your own solo with chords on the lower strings.</p>
<p><b>How can I be a good jazz guitarist?</b> Transcribe a bunch solos(and not just from guitar players); this is the best way to develop your ear, build a repertoire of licks and develop a sense of feel. Try to take them apart and figure out which licks work over which chords and see if you can apply them to different tunes in different keys, etc.</p>
