<p><b>Who is the number 1 jazz guitarist?</b> 1. Wes Montgomery. Wes Montgomery (1923-1968) was a legendary jazz guitarist known for revolutionising the world of jazz guitar with his distinctive thumb-picking technique. Born in Indianapolis, Indiana, Wes began playing guitar at a young age and was largely self-taught.</p>
