<p><b>Why are humbuckers better for jazz?</b> That's thanks to their naturally increased output and darker sonics that make your guitar's tone much thicker and chunkier. But it's not just metal and rock that's made a home for the humbucker – jazz musicians love them too! Their warm tones and rich sustain make them a favourite for clean players.</p>